d_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2020-09-08T15:10:41Z", "updated_at": "2021-05-17T11:52:11Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "ATM we hard-code fixup methods that need to run after `clone()`:\r\n\r\n- `postclone_check_head`\r\n- `postclonecfg_annexdataset`\r\n- `postclonecfg_ria`\r\n\r\nThe necessity to hard-code these things in -core is one of the primary reasons the RIA functionality had to be moved to -core.\r\n\r\nI think we should add support for custom hooks for this purpose. I am not certain about their implementation. It could be dedicated entrypoints, but it could also be a dedicated type of result hook. In both cases, the content of `results_props` (from `clone_dataset()`) must be made available to the hook.\r\n\r\nIt may be that a result hook could already perform the necessary actions - in which case this issues asks for an example to be added to the documentation.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4903/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4903/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}